\int \frac{1 + \sqrt{x+1}}{1 -1 \sqrt{x+1}} dx = \int \frac{1+t}{1-t}\times2\sqrt{t^2-1+1} dt = t^2\left(\frac{1+t}{1-t}\right) - \int t^2 \frac{2}{(t-1)^2} = \frac{t^2+t^3}{1-t} - 2t - \frac{2}{1-t} - 4 ln  (t-1) + C
\int\frac{1+\sqrt{x+1}}{1-\sqrt{x+1}}dx\\ =-\int\frac{(1+\sqrt{x+1})^2}{x}dx\\ =-\int\frac{x+2\sqrt{x+1}+2}{x}dx\\ =-\int dx-2\int\frac{dx}{x}-2\int\frac{\sqrt{x+1}}{x}dx\\ =-x-2\ln x-2(2\sqrt{x+1}+\ln\frac{\sqrt{x+1}-1}{\sqrt{x+1}+1})\\ =-x-2\ln x-4\sqrt{x+1}-2\ln\frac{(\sqrt{x+1}-1)^2}{x}\\ =-x-4\sqrt{x+1}-2\ln(\sqrt{x-1}+1)^2\\ =-x-4\sqrt{x+1}-4\ln(\sqrt{x-1}+1)
